Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.98,0:01:32.98,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(385,269.5)}Episode 31: Somewhere She'd Like
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.98,0:01:36.98,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\pos(588.5,16)}29 years after the death of Himmel the Hero,\Nin the Etwas Mountains, located in the northern lands
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.60,0:01:47.82,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It's gotten warm lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.82,0:01:50.10,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This is a volcanic area.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.10,0:01:53.20,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's an unusually warm region \Nwithin the northern lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.20,0:01:56.22,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Which means we can finally \Nenjoy some hot springs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.71,0:02:01.28,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. We'll probably \Narrive at the next village soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.28,0:02:03.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We can take a dip there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.33,0:02:22.37,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Frieren. We've been \Nwalking for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.67,0:02:24.33,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Are we there yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.62,0:02:29.87,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The village should be around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.72,0:02:35.75,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I see a cabin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.22,0:02:39.01,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Just one building.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.33,0:02:41.27,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I have a bad feeling about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.35,0:02:47.07,Default,BOY B,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.07,0:02:48.97,Default,BOY A,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.51,0:02:51.13,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.94,0:02:54.15,Default,OWNER,0000,0000,0000,,This brings back memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.48,0:02:59.16,Default,OWNER,0000,0000,0000,,The village was abandoned \Nover thirty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.40,0:03:05.07,Default,OWNER,0000,0000,0000,,The hot spring dried up, so the \Nadventurers stopped coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.41,0:03:05.90,DefaultTop,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,One at a time!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.90,0:03:08.51,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,That's a shame, isn't it, Ms. Frieren?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.16,0:03:16.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Human villages always vanish the \Nmoment you let your guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.86,0:03:20.35,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to wait until the next town \Nto enjoy the hot springs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.18,0:03:23.55,Default,SSTARK,0000,0000,0000,,How far is it to the next town?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.07,0:03:25.98,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,About a week's journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.49,0:03:29.05,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,So we have to wait a whole week.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.05,0:03:33.85,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Are there no other \Nhot springs around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.58,0:03:38.07,Default,OWNER,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.49,0:03:41.21,Default,OWNER,0000,0000,0000,,I heard from my grandfather
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.21,0:03:45.08,Default,OWNER,0000,0000,0000,,that there's a hidden hot spring \Nin the mountains back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.58,0:03:51.16,Default,OWNER,0000,0000,0000,,That was over thirty years ago, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.32,0:03:54.43,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the hidden hot spring \Nof the Etwas Mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.71,0:03:57.35,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You're familiar with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.80,0:04:00.59,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt it's still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.59,0:04:02.95,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty deep in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.95,0:04:08.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'd probably reach a hot spring sooner \Nby just heading to the next town.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.93,0:04:12.50,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Mr. Stark?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.00,0:04:15.43,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,The hidden hot spring of \Nthe Etwas Mountains...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.43,0:04:17.83,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I've heard those words before.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.75,0:04:22.31,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I remember now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.31,0:04:27.08,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, I think I'd like to visit \Nthe hidden hot spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.39,0:04:28.59,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Stark?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.03,0:04:35.42,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Stark, even though it's technically a hot \Nspring, it's really not worth the trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.42,0:04:36.29,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,After all, it's—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.29,0:04:39.52,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,We came all the way here already. \NLet's go check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.74,0:04:50.41,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. If you really want to go, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.10,0:04:54.09,Default,BOY B,0000,0000,0000,,Later, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.09,0:04:56.61,Default,BOY A,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play again!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.61,0:04:58.60,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Later!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.20,0:05:48.44,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We're almost at the hidden hot spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.96,0:05:58.51,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, you don't seem very excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.51,0:05:59.78,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.78,0:06:02.35,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I wandered through the mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.35,0:06:04.97,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,in search of the hidden hot spring \Nwith Himmel and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.67,0:06:09.36,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I want to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.36,0:06:10.43,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.56,0:06:15.47,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You traveled there with \NMr. Himmel's party, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.94,0:06:22.94,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Himmel wasn't satisfied until he searched \Nevery nook and cranny of an unusual place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.48,0:06:26.98,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,You said it'd be quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.98,0:06:29.48,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you, there's something here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.03,0:06:32.75,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I can feel it in my gut.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.58,0:06:35.35,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I told you so.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.35,0:06:37.40,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,There's no turning back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.81,0:06:42.50,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The road to the hidden hot spring \Nis especially brutal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.75,0:06:49.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You have to pass through the territory \Nof a troublesome monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.26,0:07:05.42,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's here already.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.42,0:07:06.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.65,0:07:19.92,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,A dragon, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.92,0:07:21.77,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.77,0:07:23.51,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's not a dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.51,0:07:27.48,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,If anything, that monster \Nis closer to being a lizard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.48,0:07:28.79,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,A lizard?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.11,0:07:32.92,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite agitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.92,0:07:36.56,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's typical of monsters \Nwhen their territory is invaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.04,0:07:41.07,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You have to cut off all three heads at \Nthe same time, or they'll regenerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.07,0:07:42.69,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.89,0:07:56.46,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Run, Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.47,0:07:59.19,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I have a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.57,0:08:00.99,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.49,0:08:20.90,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll split up to the left and right \Nand attack all three heads at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.90,0:08:21.69,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.05,0:08:24.77,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this in as few \Nattempts as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.56,0:08:29.44,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,If our timing is off, \Nit'll keep regenerating.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.44,0:08:30.50,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.60,0:08:34.12,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,The plan you mentioned earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.84,0:08:38.75,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll strike while the monster \Nis attacking Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.09,0:08:43.33,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.48,0:08:53.90,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I was just the bait.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.32,0:08:59.95,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Good work, both of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.93,0:09:44.02,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,We're finally here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.02,0:09:45.52,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,That was difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.11,0:09:50.35,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,See? I told you we should've just \Nheaded to the next town.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.41,0:09:53.97,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's the hidden hot spring \Nof the Etwas Mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.30,0:10:08.80,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It's so shallow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.18,0:10:12.31,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,This is just a foot bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.31,0:10:15.05,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I told you it wasn't worth the effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.09,0:10:17.92,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,This is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.49,0:10:23.78,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,This way, we can all enjoy it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.19,0:10:30.65,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.45,0:10:43.25,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,This is a nice view.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.85,0:10:44.86,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.19,0:10:50.51,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Mr. Stark, \Nwhy did you want to come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.23,0:10:53.72,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I heard about it from my master.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.12,0:10:58.71,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,The hidden hot spring of the Etwas \NMountains was just a foot bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.71,0:11:01.45,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't worth the effort at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.45,0:11:04.02,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,It was a truly ridiculous adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.56,0:11:08.35,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,It's strange, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.08,0:11:12.67,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't trade my memories
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.67,0:11:16.64,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,of those ridiculous adventures \Nwith my friends for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.07,0:11:23.83,FlashbackItalics,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never forget that view.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.70,0:11:32.99,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,So you knew, Mr. Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.39,0:11:37.88,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I think I wanted to see the \Nsame view my master saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.98,0:11:47.47,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It really is a nice view.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.42,0:12:12.90,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,The way back is brutal, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.36,0:12:22.14,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it wasn't worth \Nthe effort after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.05,0:12:28.05,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\pos(588.5,135)}29 years after the death\Nof Himmel the Hero,\Nin the fortress city of Heiß,\Nlocated in the northern lands
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.50,0:12:40.31,Default,OLD WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,You sure love hot springs \Nfor someone so young.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.20,0:12:53.83,DefaultTop,KIDS,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.20,0:12:53.83,Default,KIDS,0000,0000,0000,,Dang it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.83,0:12:55.21,Default,KIDS,0000,0000,0000,,Next game!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.97,0:13:04.33,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren has been soaking in the \Nhot springs ever since we arrived here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.33,0:13:07.72,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,When she does come out, \Nit's just to visit magic shops.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.58,0:13:11.21,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, we're staying \Nfor two more days.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.55,0:13:14.63,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's a short stay for Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.63,0:13:16.60,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I made sure to give her an earful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.56,0:13:20.47,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We have nothing to do \Nall day tomorrow, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.94,0:13:22.53,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.53,0:13:24.89,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll visit a weapon shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.89,0:13:26.46,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I need to get my axe sharpened.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.46,0:13:29.42,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, but {\i1}I'll{\i0} have nothing \Nto do all day tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.98,0:13:35.45,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Pay attention to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.83,0:13:42.59,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You're so inconsiderate, Mr. Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.59,0:13:47.13,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously? You didn't \Nhave to put it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.15,0:13:50.86,DefaultItalics,STARK/ID,0000,0000,0000,,She's always so hard on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.66,0:13:54.88,DefaultItalics,STARK/ID,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. It's time for some payback.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.59,0:14:00.02,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,If you're that desperate for attention, \Nlet's go on a date tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.67,0:14:09.24,DefaultItalics,STARK/ID,0000,0000,0000,,Oops. This never goes well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.89,0:14:15.29,DefaultItalics,STARK/ID,0000,0000,0000,,I'm dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.80,0:14:21.81,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. See you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.02,0:14:39.81,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Um, your book...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.76,0:14:45.45,DefaultItalics,STARK/ID,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd she react like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.65,0:14:59.30,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.47,0:15:15.40,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.35,0:15:22.47,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think? Is she mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.06,0:15:25.32,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What's going to happen to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.68,0:15:30.05,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Stark, do you understand \Nwho you're asking for advice?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.05,0:15:31.28,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Have you lost your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.74,0:15:35.15,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. Sorry for \Nasking the impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.15,0:15:37.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I never said it was impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.60,0:15:39.81,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a grown woman, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.81,0:15:42.02,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I know exactly how a girl thinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.72,0:15:45.66,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure? I'm trusting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.62,0:15:48.50,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let me ask you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.50,0:15:52.87,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, if I said to you, "Let's go \Non a date," what would you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.56,0:15:56.10,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You've grown into a fine man, Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.10,0:15:58.86,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so happy, I might treat you to dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.86,0:16:01.85,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, this isn't helping.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.85,0:16:05.31,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,This feels like a grandma \Nhanging out with her grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.10,0:16:07.89,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You just called me a grandma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.89,0:16:10.08,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's your second offense \Nafter calling me a hag.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.08,0:16:11.38,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You won't get away with a third.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.38,0:16:13.36,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you counting? You're scaring me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.67,0:16:16.49,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, what happens \Non the third offense?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.49,0:16:18.28,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll scream and cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.28,0:16:21.19,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,My tantrums are scary, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.19,0:16:24.30,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,They even made Himmel the Hero \Ntremble with fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.88,0:16:44.53,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,She's been crying for three \Nfull days and nights.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.53,0:16:45.55,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Yikes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.55,0:16:46.60,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.86,0:16:48.49,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.49,0:16:51.03,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Is that how a grown woman behaves?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.73,0:16:59.29,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I understand now that you're \Nentirely lacking in tact and sensitivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.29,0:17:03.69,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,So, are you going on a date with Fern?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.62,0:17:09.39,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't feel like \NI can take it back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.39,0:17:13.49,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,So I thought I'd ask you to suggest \Nsome places she might like.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.32,0:17:18.00,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, never mind. \NI shouldn't have asked—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.00,0:17:19.38,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Should we go take a look, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.38,0:17:20.25,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.25,0:17:21.92,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I can probably find somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.44,0:17:24.85,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Somewhere she'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.78,0:17:27.07,Default,PASSERSBY,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.07,0:17:28.44,Default,PASSERSBY,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we get something to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.44,0:17:29.41,Default,PASSERSBY,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.62,0:17:32.68,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You should start by getting her \Nsomething to eat at the market.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.19,0:17:35.96,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,She gets cranky when she's hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.28,0:17:39.18,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't skip the food stalls.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.68,0:17:42.98,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fern has loved snacking \Nsince she was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.43,0:17:50.83,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,She'd probably like shops \Nwith pretty items on display.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.74,0:17:56.75,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fern likes baked goods, but what \Nshe wants depends on her mood,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.67,0:18:01.58,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,so you should choose a few dessert shops.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.49,0:18:09.05,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What else...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.87,0:18:20.78,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet plazas like these \Nare an option, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.49,0:18:26.08,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously? You know Fern really well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.08,0:18:28.26,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed, Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.26,0:18:31.03,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.30,0:18:34.06,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.52,0:18:36.61,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Heiter was the impressive one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.28,0:18:43.02,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,He talked about Fern's \Npreferences all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.28,0:18:46.94,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,"She gets cranky when she's hungry,"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.94,0:18:50.89,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,"she likes snacking," \N"she likes pretty things,"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.75,0:18:57.67,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,and "her preferences change depending on \Nher mood" are all things Heiter taught me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.73,0:19:05.71,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Heiter seemed to want me to be \Na parental figure to Fern,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.46,0:19:11.67,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,but ultimately, I failed \Nto discover anything she liked.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.36,0:19:23.13,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,But you remember all of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.00,0:19:27.71,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I think you're a good parent to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.52,0:19:32.87,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.87,0:19:37.75,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,we first celebrated Fern's birthday \Non the road in a place like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.24,0:19:45.04,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You have some nice things \Nto say sometimes, Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.81,0:19:46.95,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.71,0:19:51.61,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll strike one offense from the record.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.29,0:19:53.63,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.41,0:20:23.78,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, I was asked out on a date.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.37,0:20:25.77,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.22,0:20:28.74,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.26,0:20:32.25,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.87,0:20:37.37,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, have you \Never been on a date?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.37,0:20:38.64,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.64,0:20:40.00,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Of course you haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.11,0:20:43.87,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you have?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.08,0:20:44.88,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.12,0:20:51.67,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Who did you go with, and what did you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.24,0:20:55.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Himmel and I went looking for a lost cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.01,0:20:58.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We were asked to by the owner \Nof a magic item shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.16,0:21:02.97,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,So you were just completing a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.41,0:21:07.05,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure you can call that a date.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.81,0:21:12.56,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Fern,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.56,0:21:16.02,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,when two close friends of opposing sex \Ngo out with each other and nobody else,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.02,0:21:18.43,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,that's a date.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.35,0:21:23.41,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's what my master said.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.50,0:21:29.70,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, I went \Non a date with Sein, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.70,0:21:31.05,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.06,0:21:37.48,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.98,0:22:25.11,Credits,CREDITS,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(526,517)\fs10\pos(525,120)}Translation\N{\fs12}Sho Stifler\N\N{\fs10}Editing & Typesetting\N{\fs12}Geoff Mazzolini\N\N{\fs10}Subtitle Timing\N{\fs12}Edgar Cruz\N\N{\fs10}Quality Check\N{\fs12}Alicia Ashby\N\N{\fs10}Translation Check\N{\fs12}Elizabeth Ellis
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.20,0:23:52.59,Default,GUARD,0000,0000,0000,,So you're the first-class mage Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.02,0:23:54.44,DefaultTop,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't expecting to find \Nsuch a powerful monster here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.49,0:23:53.58,DefaultOverlap,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You're not wearing your usual clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.57,0:23:55.10,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,So, where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.82,0:23:55.09,DefaultOverlap,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I was going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.88,0:23:57.34,DefaultTop,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,We were born and raised here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.09,0:23:56.79,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let your guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.34,0:24:00.11,Default,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I want to protect \Nother people's homes, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.62,0:24:00.07,Signs_NextEp,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(229,1)\blur3\t(20,312,\blur0.2)\pos(320,113.5)\c&H000000&\t(312,646,\c&HF6F6F6&)\fsp1.6\t(\fsp1)}Episode 32\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NOther People's Homes